Xianya, you continue to disappoint.<br>
<br>
Apep has indeed planned a fine RP event.  Yes, it is disappointing that the GM's won't get involved so that it could really become something spectacular.<br>
<br>
What I see is strictly from a gamers viewpoint.  You can't possibly win in this scenario, so you decide the best thing to do is to cheat and use something that would never exist.. LAG.<br>
<br>
Whomever made the suggestion of everyone joining a particular guild and then declaring /guildwar hit the nail on the head.  You want Verant to get involved when you yourselves aren't doing what is already made available to you in order to have the results you wish.<br>
<br>
There is NO reason you can't leave your current guilds and join one side or the other and then release a total free-for-all, no reason other than that you don't want to.<br>
<br>
Instead, you would rather lag out the entire zone.  You would rather destroy not just the roleplaying but the entire game for many people.  It saddens me that I have seen only limited consideration for the results of such.  This blatant lack of consideration for others is WHY so many have left Tinkers Pride in favor of the Gnomish Alliance Group.  When will you learn?<br>
<br>
The suggestion to switch to alternative guilds and declare guildwar is the most plausible and accomplishes what so many speak of wanting to do.<br>
<br>
Apep, I have no doubt that you WOULD encourage switching to a guild and an opposing guild to make this happen. <br>
<br>
Defenders?  Just how stalwart are you?  Dare you join a temporary guild and be set upon by the likes of Gore Bloodlust?<br>
<br>
To those of you who have argued against using LAG and other in-game inconsistencies, I do indeed salute you and your sense of fair play which allows everyone to enjoy the game.  To the rest of you I say but one thing: <br>
<br>
It's time to put up or shut up.  <br>
<br>
Join opposing guilds, declare guildwar, and let nature take its course where the strong shall devour the weak.<br>
<br>
Good luck!<br>
